# Changelog

All notable changes to the Windows Service & Process Monitoring Agent are documented here.

---

## [2.0.0] ‚Äî 2026-04-23

### Added
- Full modular pipeline architecture with 5 independent detection modules
- `ParentChildAnalyzer` ‚Äî detects 15+ forbidden parent-child process relationships
- `StartupServiceAuditor` ‚Äî WMI-based service enumeration with path and command analysis
- `UnauthorizedProcessDetector` ‚Äî whitelist/blacklist engine with 50+ approved processes
- `ReportGenerator` ‚Äî structured JSON reports + colour-coded console summaries
- Simulation mode for non-Windows systems (full demo with realistic threat scenarios)
- MITRE ATT&CK technique mapping on every alert (T1059, T1543.003, T1036, T1003, T1055)
- CLI interface with `--continuous`, `--interval`, and `--output` flags
- Severity-tiered alerting: CRITICAL / HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW / INFO
- High-risk process blacklist: mimikatz, nc.exe, procdump, meterpreter and 15+ more
- Suspicious directory detection: Temp, Public, ProgramData, AppData
- Timestamped event logging to file and console simultaneously

### Detection Rules Added
- R-001 to R-010 covering Office macro abuse, LOTL attacks, service persistence, masquerading

---

## [1.0.0] ‚Äî 2026-03-01

### Added
- Initial proof-of-concept process enumerator using psutil
- Basic parent-child relationship check for winword.exe and excel.exe
- Simple text-based console output
- Single-scan mode only